comments.body:
Simple documentation of theming: 
1. Add thumbnail image named as `{theme-name}_preview.png` to themes directory for each theme. (example: `app/assets/images/spotlight/themes/default_preview.png`)
2. Create stylesheets for each theme with a naming convention of `application_{theme-name}.scss` (note: application.scss is the default theme)
3. Remove ` *= require_tree .` line from `application.scss`
4. Add `Rails.application.config.assets.precompile += %w( application_{theme-name}.css )` to `/config/initializers/assets.rb`
5. Add `Spotlight::Engine.config.exhibit_themes = %w[{theme-name} default]` to `/config/initializers/spotlight_initializer.rb`
Not sure if we need typekit or not, but added it in case.
